parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when it occurs at high speeds or when the driver is not expecting it.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates or surges forward
often when the driver is braking or slowing down
and may continue to accelerate even when the driver applies the brakes. In some cases
the vehicle may accelerate rapidly
reaching high speeds in a short amount of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the vehicle to lose braking capability, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: ABS and VSC warning indicators illuminate
fuel odor emitted from the vehicle
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
vehicle accelerates unintentionally
vehicle lurches forward when brakes are applied
humming noise when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of defective brake parts can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brakes squeak
brake parts need to be replaced frequently
brake failure occurs despite recent replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates unintentionally
vehicle lurches forward when brakes are applied
vehicle accelerates when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking capability, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: ABS warning indicator illuminates
vehicle has little stopping ability
ABS activates below 5 mph when coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front End Vibration and Steering Wheel Shake
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive vibration and steering wheel shake can cause loss of control, increased stopping distance, and accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes abnormally
the front end of the vehicle vibrates excessively
the vibration is felt at high speeds (50-75 mph)
the vibration persists despite wheel balance and alignment attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the front end of the vehicle to drop, leading to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle drops to the ground
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to steer.
